# Omninuera

## Offer Letter — AI Intern

Date: [Start Date]

Dear [Candidate Full Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship with Omninuera for the role of **AI Intern** on the following terms and conditions.

### 1. Position
Role: AI Intern  
Reporting to: [Reporting Manager]

### 2. Duration
This internship engagement is for a fixed period of **3 months**, commencing on [Start Date] (the "Internship Period"), unless earlier terminated in accordance with the Termination clause below.

### 3. Stipend
You will receive a **stipend** of **INR 10,000 (Ten Thousand Indian Rupees)** per month. This amount is expressly a stipend for the internship engagement and not a salary or wages under/for any employment benefits.

### 4. Work Location and Hours
- Work location: **Fully remote**. Candidate is expected to be based in **Bengaluru** during the Internship Period.  
- Expected weekly commitment: **Approximately 20–40 hours per week**, with flexibility to manage working times given the remote arrangement. Specific working patterns should be coordinated with your Reporting Manager.

### 5. Nature of Engagement
This is an internship / temporary engagement. You are not entitled to any employee benefits (such as health insurance, provident fund, gratuity, paid leave, or employee stock options) unless such benefits are explicitly agreed in writing by Omninuera.

### 6. Key Responsibilities
During the Internship Period your primary responsibilities will include, but are not limited to:
- Data collection, cleaning and preparation for model training and evaluation.
- Designing and running model experiments and prototyping ML solutions.
- Evaluating model performance and producing reproducible evaluation reports.
- Writing clear documentation, experiment logs, and summaries of findings.
- Collaborating with team members across engineering and research to integrate work into broader projects.

### 7. Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
- You agree to keep confidential all proprietary and non-public information of Omninuera that you access or learn during the Internship Period. Confidentiality obligations will continue after the Internship Period ends.
- You agree that all inventions, discoveries, designs, developments, works of authorship, improvements, algorithms, code, data sets, documentation, and other intellectual property (collectively, "Work Product") that you create, conceive, reduce to practice, or develop, either alone or jointly with others, during the Internship Period and which relate to Omninuera's business or arise from your activities for Omninuera, shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera. You hereby assign (and agree to assign) to Omninuera all right, title and interest in and to such Work Product, and you agree to sign any documents and take any steps reasonably requested by Omninuera to effectuate such assignment.

### 8. Termination / Early Exit
- Either party may terminate this agreement with **one (1) week written notice** to the other party.
- Omninuera may terminate your internship **immediately for cause**, which includes but is not limited to gross misconduct, breach of confidentiality, material breach of these terms, or illegal activity.

### 9. Stipend Payment Schedule
- The stipend will be paid **monthly** by bank transfer to the account details you provide.  
- Please provide the following bank details for stipend payment: **[Bank Account Details for Stipend]**.  
- Stipend payments are subject to applicable tax withholding as required by law.

### 10. Conditions
- This offer is **subject to** completion of any required background verification and legal/compliance review by Omninuera.  
- This offer is conditional and may be withdrawn if background verification reveals information that, in Omninuera’s reasonable judgment, makes you unsuitable for the role.

### 11. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
This agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising out of or in connection with this agreement shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in Bengaluru, India.

### 12. Acceptance
To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy to your Reporting Manager or the HR contact.

